    <div class="container-fluid text-center img-circle" style="background-color:olive">
    h1 Jaybot7 API Basejump: Timestamp microservice<BR>
    h2 User stories:
    ul
        li 1) I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: January 1, 2016)
        li 2) If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.
        li 3) If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.    
    
    p2 If you did all that, you should see the 
    h1 RESULT here:<BR>
    p3= message
    
    h2 Example usage
    p http://timestampper.herokuapp.com/December 2015 202015
    p http://timestampper.herokuapp.com/1450137600

    h3 Example output:{ "unix": 1450137600, "natural": "December 15, 2015" }
